@context: Automation Practice Gauntlet (testautomationpractice.blogspot.com). Includes text inputs, radio/checkboxes, dropdowns, date pickers, drag-and-drop, dynamic tables with pagination, and Shadow DOM.
@title: complex_ui_full_inspection


STEP 1: Navigate to practice page
    NAVIGATE to https://testautomationpractice.blogspot.com/

STEP 2: Text inputs
    # Fill detects the "input" interaction mode from keywords like
    # "fill", "type", "enter". The engine resolves the target by
    # heuristic scoring — quoted text gets the strongest signal.
    FILL 'Name' field with 'Mega Manul'
    FILL 'Email' field with 'mega@manul.ai'
    FILL 'Phone' field with '9876543210'
    # Adding "textarea" outside the quotes acts as an element-type hint,
    # boosting the score for <textarea> tags over <input> tags.
    FILL 'Address' field with 'Selenium Avenue, 42, AI City'
    VERIFY that 'Mega Manul' is present

STEP 3: Radio button and checkboxes
    # Including "radio button" or "checkbox" outside the target quotes
    # triggers strict mode scoring: non-matching element types get a
    # heavy penalty (-50,000), preventing accidental clicks on <td> or
    # <label> elements that share the same text.
    CLICK the radio button for 'Male'
    VERIFY that 'Male' is checked
    CHECK the checkbox for 'Monday'
    VERIFY that 'Monday' is checked
    CHECK the checkbox for 'Tuesday'
    VERIFY that 'Tuesday' is checked
    CHECK the checkbox for 'Thursday'
    VERIFY that 'Thursday' is checked

STEP 4: Selection lists
    # "Select ... from ... dropdown" uses Playwright's select_option()
    # for native <select> elements. If the target is a custom div-based
    # dropdown, the engine gracefully falls back to click().
    SELECT 'Japan' from the 'Country' dropdown
    VERIFY that 'Japan' is present
    SELECT 'Blue' from the 'Colors' dropdown

STEP 5: Date picker and interactive buttons
    FILL 'Date Picker 1' field with '12/31/2026'
    SCROLL DOWN
    CLICK the 'START' button
    # DOUBLE CLICK is detected as a "clickable" mode and uses
    # Playwright's dblclick() instead of click().
    DOUBLE CLICK the 'Copy Text' button
    VERIFY that 'Hello World!' is present

STEP 6: Drag and drop
    # Drag-and-drop resolves two elements (source and destination)
    # and uses Playwright's drag_to(). Both targets are quoted.
    DRAG the element 'Drag me to my target' and drop it into 'Drop here'
    VERIFY that 'Dropped!' is present

STEP 7: Data extraction from web table
    SCROLL DOWN
    # EXTRACT captures text into runtime variables {chrome_cpu}, etc.
    # These variables live in engine memory and can be referenced in
    # later steps with {placeholder} syntax.
    EXTRACT the 'CPU of Chrome' into {chrome_cpu}
    EXTRACT the 'CPU of Firefox' into {firefox_cpu}
    EXTRACT the 'Price of Master In Selenium' into {book_price}
    EXTRACT the 'Price of Selenium' into {selenium_price}
    VERIFY that '3000' is present

STEP 8: Paginated table interaction
    SCROLL DOWN
    CLICK on the '2' link
    CHECK the checkbox for '7'
    CLICK on the '4' link
    CHECK the checkbox for '17'

STEP 9: Scrolling dropdown
    SCROLL DOWN
    CLICK the 'Scrolling DropDown' element
    # "SCROLL DOWN inside the list" targets the first dropdown-style
    # scroll container and sets scrollTop = scrollHeight.
    SCROLL DOWN inside the list
    CLICK the 'Item 100' element
    # VERIFY that 'Item 100' is present

STEP 10: Shadow DOM input
    # Shadow DOM elements are discovered by the TreeWalker in
    # SNAPSHOT_JS. Interactions use JS fallback helpers
    # (window.manulClick, window.manulType) when Playwright's
    # native locators cannot reach inside the shadow root.
    SCROLL DOWN
    TYPE 'Shadow Boss' into the 'Shadow Root' field
    VERIFY that 'Shadow Boss' is present

STEP 11: Final validation
    # A multi-assertion VERIFY — all quoted tokens must be present
    # in the visible page text for this step to pass.
    # VERIFY that 'Mega Manul' is present
    VERIFY that 'Japan' is present
    VERIFY that 'Dropped!' is present
    # VERIFY that 'Item 100' is present
    VERIFY that 'Shadow Boss' is present
DONE.
